-- PRESS DIGEST -Hong Kong - Jan 30 
-- By Yimou Lee
-- Wed Jan 29, 2014 08:54PM EST
-- None



HONG KONG, Jan 30 (Reuters) - These are some of the leading stories in Hong Kong newspapers on Thursday. Reuters has not verified these stories and does not vouch for their accuracy.

SOUTH CHINA MORNING POST  -- Internet company Tencent Holdings Ltd <0700.HK> is expanding its maps function by dispatching a fleet of camera cars to create the most comprehensive street view on the mainland. (http://link.reuters.com/pux46v) -- Lawmakers want the government to speed up its numerous financial reform plans and to go further in helping local financial professionals enter the many planned free-trade zones in the mainland. (http://link.reuters.com/qux46v)  THE STANDARD -- Offering tax incentives to overseas companies would create an unfair tax environment and weaken the local tax base, said Secretary for Financial Services and the Treasury Ceajer Chan Ka-keung. (http://link.reuters.com/hux46v) -- Hutchison Whampoa <0013.HK> remains confident of completing its HK$8.24 billion ($1.06 billion) purchase of a telecom business in Ireland that is currently subject to European regulatory reviews. (http://link.reuters.com/mux46v) -- Lenovo Group <0992.HK> will pay IBM a fee more than double the typical size should it fail to acquire IBM's low-end server unit, people familiar with the matter said. Lenovo agreed to pay a reverse break-up fee of 8 percent to 9 percent of the $2.3 billion purchase price. (http://link.reuters.com/kux46v) -- HK Electric Investments <2638.HK> Chairman Canning Fok Kin-ning stressed the trust could generate a yield of more than 7 percent after it closed below the offer price on its trading debut. (http://link.reuters.com/nux46v) -- Prices of new homes plunged by 10 to 20 percent last year, prompting builders to offer hefty discounts, development secretary Paul Chan Mo-po said. (http://link.reuters.com/sux46v)  HONG KONG ECONOMIC JOURNAL  -- Shimao Property's <0813.HK> subsidiary in China purchased 7.7 percent shares in Shenyin & Wanguo Securities for HK$2.8 billion yuan, making it the third largest shareholder in the brokerage. -- Second home transactions in Hong Kong's 10 major housing estates dropped 13.4 percent in January to 149 deals, the third lowest on record.  HONG KONG ECONOMIC TIMES  -- Hong Kong's major developers, including Cheung Kong (Holdings) Ltd <0001.HK>, Sun Hung Kai Properties <0016.HK> and Henderson Land Development <0012.HK>, are expected to put a total of more than 1,700 new units on sale during the Lunar New Year holidays.   ORIENTAL DAILY NEWS -- Hong Kong's new mortgage loans dropped 23.7 percent to HK$158.6 billion in 2013 from a year earlier, the lowest in seven years. -- Transactions in Hong Kong's leading commercial properties dropped 56.9 percent to HK$1.84 billion from a year earlier in 2013, the lowest in 10 years, according to Centaline Property Agency.  TA KUNG PAO -- Logan Property Holdings Co Ltd <3380.HK> won a bid for three land slots in Guangdong's Shantou city for 1.96 billion yuan.  -- The number of private home completions in Hong Kong is expected to exceed 15,800 units as developers speed up sales, according to Centaline Property Agency.